- Look, what did I tell you
when you applied for the job?

32:01.934 --> 32:04.367
I promised your father
as he was dying

32:04.433 --> 32:05.700
that I'd take care of you.

32:05.767 --> 32:09.600
I'm not letting you
anywhere near the prisoners.

32:10.600 --> 32:12.300
- Then I quit.

32:12.367 --> 32:13.633
I'll go get a job
in another prison

32:13.700 --> 32:15.400
where they'll let me
deal with the inmates.

32:15.467 --> 32:17.600
♪ ♪

32:17.667 --> 32:19.667
- What the hell
you trying to prove, huh?

32:19.734 --> 32:20.834
That you're as tough
as your dad?

32:20.900 --> 32:22.834
Clayton, he died in here,

32:22.900 --> 32:24.500
his heart beating in my arms,

32:24.567 --> 32:26.166
and I'm not going through
the same thing with you.

32:26.233 --> 32:29.000
- I'm not ten years old
anymore, Leo.

32:29.066 --> 32:31.100
You can't stop me.

32:34.734 --> 32:37.667
[tense percussive tones]

32:37.734 --> 32:39.500
♪ ♪

32:39.567 --> 32:43.600
- We'll figure this out
tomorrow, okay?

32:48.734 --> 32:51.367
- Hey, give me your keys.
- No, I can drive myself.

32:51.433 --> 32:54.467
This conversation
just sobered me up.

32:56.266 --> 32:59.367
♪ ♪

32:59.433 --> 33:02.033
- Whoa! Whoa!
