33:09.266 --> 33:10.200
- Fuck off!

33:10.266 --> 33:12.133
You ain't so bad now, huh?

33:12.200 --> 33:13.433
Huh?

33:18.734 --> 33:20.133
Who's the man, huh?

33:20.200 --> 33:22.600
Fuck you! Who? Who?

33:22.667 --> 33:24.600
[yells]

33:26.166 --> 33:29.233
[shouting]

33:29.300 --> 33:31.333
- Take him to the Hole.

33:33.567 --> 33:35.700
- You okay?

33:35.767 --> 33:37.967
Go to the hospital.
Get yourself checked out.

33:38.033 --> 33:39.934
- I'm okay.

33:41.367 --> 33:42.433
- What's this about?

33:42.500 --> 33:44.467
- Motherfuckin' spic
is crazy.

33:44.533 --> 33:47.567
Mumbling some shit
about his mother, man.

33:49.767 --> 33:52.066
- The fuck you looking at?

33:52.133 --> 33:55.166
[men drumming and singing]

34:18.533 --> 34:22.066
- Napoleon's final defeat
came at Waterloo.

34:22.133 --> 34:23.667
It must have been embarrassing.

34:23.734 --> 34:25.166
You're the fuckin' emperor,

34:25.233 --> 34:27.300
you conquered all of Europe,
only to lose in a place

34:27.367 --> 34:30.133
with a stupid name
like Waterloo,

34:30.200 --> 34:33.000
or Watergate or Whitewater.

34:33.066 --> 34:36.233
Note to politicians:
stay on land.

34:36.300 --> 34:38.333
- Well, Larry,
ever since we reinstituted

34:38.400 --> 34:40.667
the death penalty,
the courts have been clogged

34:40.734 --> 34:43.500
with needless appeals
by convicted murderers

34:43.567 --> 34:45.367
trying to escape
their rightful punishment.

34:45.433 --> 34:49.500
So the legislature has agreed
to reduce fees paid

34:49.567 --> 34:52.200
to court-appointed lawyers
in murder cases,

34:52.266 --> 34:53.500
and some of these lawyers,

34:53.567 --> 34:55.667
who are against
capital punishment,

34:55.734 --> 34:58.500
have been padding their bills
in order to say,

34:58.567 --> 35:01.333
"You see, it's too expensive."

35:01.400 --> 35:05.700
Well, I say, let them
take advantage of taxpayers

35:05.767 --> 35:07.767
somewhere else.

35:07.834 --> 35:10.533
- The court rejected our appeal.
- Oh.

35:10.600 --> 35:12.300
So what's the next step?

35:12.367 --> 35:14.700
- Well, normally,
the next step--

35:14.767 --> 35:17.867
the last step--
is the state supreme court.

35:17.934 --> 35:19.967
- Well, let's do that then.

35:21.166 --> 35:23.800
What's the matter, Lawrence?

35:23.867 --> 35:26.633
- I'm recusing myself
as your attorney.

35:26.700 --> 35:28.700
- What?

35:30.867 --> 35:34.367
Why? Was it something I said?
Something I did?

35:34.433 --> 35:36.000
- Not at all.

35:36.066 --> 35:38.834
It's just that
with these new lower fees

35:38.900 --> 35:41.500
that the state's paying,

35:41.567 --> 35:43.734
I can't afford
to work on your defense.

35:43.800 --> 35:46.100
Murder cases are complicated.

35:46.166 --> 35:49.500
They take a lot of time,
and I've been neglecting

35:49.567 --> 35:50.834
the rest of my practice.

35:50.900 --> 35:52.567
- What will happen to me then?

35:52.633 --> 35:55.500
- The court will appoint you
another lawyer.

35:55.567 --> 35:58.500
- One that won't be as good.

35:58.567 --> 36:00.834
Because the ones that take
the jobs with the lower rates

36:00.900 --> 36:02.867
are the ones
no one else will hire.

36:02.934 --> 36:04.500
- I'm sorry.

36:09.500 --> 36:16.533
