36:47.734 --> 36:49.000
- Hi, Dad.

36:49.066 --> 36:51.500
- Vern, I've got bad news.

36:51.567 --> 36:52.934
- The only kind of news
you ever got.

36:53.000 --> 36:54.800
- Andy has been arrested.

36:54.867 --> 36:57.133
- Christ. For what?

36:57.200 --> 36:58.133
- I don't know.

36:58.200 --> 37:00.834
Drugs. Beating up some nigger.

37:00.900 --> 37:02.500
The lawyer's trying
to sort it out.

37:02.567 --> 37:04.500
- Which lawyer?
Don't use Zanger.

37:04.567 --> 37:06.433
- No,
the court-appointed lawyer.

37:06.500 --> 37:08.333
- A public defender?

37:08.400 --> 37:10.567
Hire a real fucking attorney,
Dad.

37:10.633 --> 37:11.767
- I don't have the money, Vern.

37:11.834 --> 37:13.266
I talked to the PD
on the phone.

37:13.333 --> 37:14.533
She sounds smart.

37:14.600 --> 37:17.333
- She? What's her name?

37:17.400 --> 37:18.967
- I don't know.

37:19.033 --> 37:21.967
I think it's Goldberg.

37:22.033 --> 37:23.300
- Jesus fuckin' Christ, Dad.

37:23.367 --> 37:25.033
I need you to take care of this.

37:25.100 --> 37:27.300
- What the fuck do you think
I'm doing?

37:27.367 --> 37:29.133
And I'm gonna tell you
one thing.

37:29.200 --> 37:31.734
I ain't throwing good money
after bad,

37:31.800 --> 37:34.967
and your two boys are bad.

37:35.033 --> 37:38.266
- Yeah, well,
the apple doesn't fall very far.

37:38.333 --> 37:40.200
♪ ♪

37:46.133 --> 37:48.867
- You wanted to see me?

37:57.734 --> 38:00.133
- I gotta get out of this place.

38:00.200 --> 38:01.834
- There's a reason
you're in protective custody.

38:01.900 --> 38:05.500
We want you to live long enough
to testify against Schillinger.

38:05.567 --> 38:09.266
- Hey, Warden, I stay
in here, I die of boredom.

38:09.333 --> 38:12.133
- You wanted magazines.
I sent magazines.

38:12.200 --> 38:14.600
- How many times a day
can a guy jerk off?

38:14.667 --> 38:16.300
- I don't know.
It depends on the guy.

38:16.367 --> 38:18.166
- I got to go back to Em City.

38:18.233 --> 38:19.467
I ain't worried
about Schillinger.

38:19.533 --> 38:21.433
I'll take care of myself.

38:21.500 --> 38:25.166
I want that fuck to see
that I'm not punking out.

38:25.233 --> 38:27.133
- What the fuck is she wearing
for a bra?

38:27.200 --> 38:29.633
- Hey, Keller. Back so soon?

38:29.700 --> 38:32.934
- Ain't no Miss Sally
in protective custody.

38:56.734 --> 38:58.767
- Don't.

39:07.066 --> 39:09.100
- Do you realize
we've only kissed once?

39:13.333 --> 39:16.700
In all these months, once.

39:19.166 --> 39:21.934
All I've been thinking about
is kissing you again.

39:22.000 --> 39:23.500
- Hey, I said don't.

39:23.567 --> 39:26.934
- Beecher, you fuck.
I did what you asked!

39:27.000 --> 39:29.133
I ratted out
Schillinger and Metzger.

39:29.200 --> 39:32.266
You know what that means.

39:32.333 --> 39:34.734
Toby, you know
what that cost me?

39:36.033 --> 39:37.967
- Unless this is
just another scheme

39:38.033 --> 39:40.166
you and Schillinger
cooked up.

39:40.233 --> 39:43.467
How am I supposed
to trust you?

39:43.533 --> 39:46.467
Put myself
in that position again?

39:46.533 --> 39:48.333
Be that vulnerable again?

39:57.433 --> 39:58.967
[spits]

40:24.500 --> 40:27.333
- Keller knows if he fucks
with me, he's a dead man.

40:31.533 --> 40:34.567
- [faint murmuring]

40:38.767 --> 40:40.767
- Yo!

40:50.433 --> 40:51.700
Well, if you're coming,
motherfucker,

40:51.767 --> 40:53.800
come on and bring it!

40:59.100 --> 41:01.200
[grunts]

41:14.734 --> 41:17.166
- I need that crash cart
right away.

41:17.233 --> 41:18.333
We need to start an IV.

41:18.400 --> 41:19.834
I need some Vaseline, gauze,

41:19.900 --> 41:21.100
and some combine.

41:21.166 --> 41:22.333
- [wheezes]

41:22.400 --> 41:24.433
- I think he may have
a punctured lung.

41:26.400 --> 41:29.166
- Well, Mr. Keller's got about
three or four assholes now.

41:29.233 --> 41:31.266
[laughter]

41:50.300 --> 41:52.533
- You asked to be assigned
to the kitchen again.

41:52.600 --> 41:55.200
Now you're saying
you don't want to work there?

41:55.266 --> 41:57.100
- There's too many bad memories.

41:57.166 --> 42:00.367
Bad feelings.

42:00.433 --> 42:02.467
Nappa, Wangler...

42:03.934 --> 42:05.700
They don't trust me.

42:05.767 --> 42:09.367
I don't trust them.

42:09.433 --> 42:13.133
I'm don't want to fall back
into my old ways.

42:13.200 --> 42:16.166
- Well, the dress factory's
always looking for new workers.

42:16.233 --> 42:18.667
- No.

42:18.734 --> 42:22.166
If I can, I would like
to work in the AIDS ward.

42:22.233 --> 42:24.800
- Well, we don't get many
volunteers for the AIDS ward.

42:24.867 --> 42:30.500
- In Africa,
AIDS is much worse than here.

42:30.567 --> 42:34.166
I would like to learn
something about the disease

42:34.233 --> 42:38.834
so maybe, some day...

42:38.900 --> 42:41.300
I can help my people.

42:41.367 --> 42:48.300
♪ ♪

42:48.367 --> 42:51.533
- Now, these men are in
the final stages of the disease.

42:51.600 --> 42:53.533
We can't do much more
than make them comfortable

42:53.600 --> 42:55.700
and treat them with dignity.

42:55.767 --> 42:58.367
Now, Robbie Gerth needs
his medicine.

42:58.433 --> 43:00.000
Bed seven.

43:12.200 --> 43:13.133
- Who are you?

43:13.200 --> 43:15.000
- Adebisi.

43:15.066 --> 43:17.100
Take these.

43:22.367 --> 43:24.266
- Yummy.

43:26.233 --> 43:28.867
I didn't come to Oz with AIDS.

43:28.934 --> 43:30.967
I caught it like the brass ring.

43:32.567 --> 43:35.333
You ever fuck anybody
up the ass?

43:35.400 --> 43:36.834
- Yes.

43:36.900 --> 43:39.600
- You protected?

43:39.667 --> 43:40.600
- No.

43:40.667 --> 43:42.600
- Tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk.

43:42.667 --> 43:45.166
- Dr. Nathan asked me to take
some more blood from you.

43:45.233 --> 43:47.633
- She just took my blood
a minute ago.

43:47.700 --> 43:49.266
- She dropped it.

43:55.533 --> 43:58.600
[gate buzzes]

44:15.867 --> 44:18.033
- Ow!

44:18.100 --> 44:20.800
Adebisi, you just pinch me?

44:20.867 --> 44:22.900
- No, boss.

44:27.734 --> 44:30.667
- History tells us that Napoleon
was the first guy to utter,

44:30.734 --> 44:33.500
"If you want something done
right, do it yourself."

44:33.567 --> 44:35.333
But how can they be sure?

44:35.400 --> 44:37.333
I mean, what if ol' Napoleon's
butcher said it to him

44:37.400 --> 44:39.000
while slicing up some salami,

44:39.066 --> 44:40.834
and Napoleon,
being no dummy, said,

44:40.900 --> 44:43.166
"I got to write that down"?

44:43.233 --> 44:46.266
[men drumming and singing]

45:00.467 --> 45:03.367
- [panting]

45:05.266 --> 45:07.000
[yells]

45:14.667 --> 45:17.133
- Miguel Alvarez is showing
increased signs of agitation

45:17.200 --> 45:19.700
since Dr. Garvey
took him off Zoloft.

45:19.767 --> 45:20.900
- Well, that's no surprise.

45:20.967 --> 45:22.133
- And I can't say for sure,

45:22.200 --> 45:26.133
but, uh,
he really looks thinner.

45:26.200 --> 45:28.467
- I doubt that's a reaction
to the withdrawal.

45:28.533 --> 45:31.633
- You don't suppose
Dr. Garvey would change his mind

45:31.700 --> 45:33.900
and put Alvarez back
on antidepressants.

45:33.967 --> 45:36.133
- No. He's not a doctor.

45:36.200 --> 45:37.667
He's a walking ledger.

45:37.734 --> 45:39.667
Every decision he makes
is based on maintaining

45:39.734 --> 45:42.333
the HMO's profit margin.

45:42.400 --> 45:44.333
I have an interview with him
in a few minutes,

45:44.400 --> 45:46.000
during which he'll decide
whether or not he wants

45:46.066 --> 45:47.533
to keep me on staff.

45:47.600 --> 45:49.633
- What are you saying?

45:51.567 --> 45:53.800
- I'm saying
it may be time to go.

45:54.300 --> 45:56.333
- Dr. Nathan, Rebadow's awake.

45:56.400 --> 45:57.767
- Thank you.

45:57.834 --> 45:59.266
- What's going on with Rebadow?

45:59.333 --> 46:03.233
- He went into insulin shock.
He's got diabetes.

46:03.300 --> 46:05.500
- Diabetes?

46:05.567 --> 46:07.333
I don't have diabetes.

46:07.400 --> 46:09.467
- You do now.

46:09.533 --> 46:12.800
This happens sometimes
later in life.

46:12.867 --> 46:16.467
- The body starts
shutting down.

46:16.533 --> 46:18.800
- You'll have to take
injections regularly,

46:18.867 --> 46:22.467
go on dialysis weekly,
and alter your diet.

46:22.533 --> 46:25.533
- Mom's fudge.

46:25.600 --> 46:27.133
My mother makes the best fudge.

46:27.200 --> 46:29.300
She sends me a batch
once a month.

46:32.033 --> 46:33.300
- Well, I guess
you'll have to be satisfied

46:33.367 --> 46:34.934
with the food in the cafeteria.

46:38.633 --> 46:40.767
- Now, let's see.

46:40.834 --> 46:44.834
You've worked here at Oswald
almost two years.

46:44.900 --> 46:47.667
Do you like working here?

46:47.734 --> 46:50.166
- If you're asking me
whether I enjoy myself,

46:50.233 --> 46:52.667
I'd have to say no.

46:52.734 --> 46:54.667
- Then why do you want to stay?

46:54.734 --> 46:57.333
- Because what we do here
is important.

46:57.400 --> 46:59.834
There's a real need
for proper health care.

46:59.900 --> 47:04.100
- Yeah, "proper" health care,
not excessive.

47:04.166 --> 47:05.333
I know you don't support

47:05.400 --> 47:07.300
the privatization of the system
here at Oz,

47:07.367 --> 47:10.333
but by paying Weigert
a fixed rate,

47:10.400 --> 47:12.767
no matter what care
the inmate requires,

47:12.834 --> 47:14.934
the state reduces its costs.

47:15.000 --> 47:17.300
- But because Weigert gets paid
the same amount

47:17.367 --> 47:19.533
no matter what treatment
we prescribe,

47:19.600 --> 47:22.934
wouldn't you limit my ability
to call in specialists

47:23.000 --> 47:23.934
or to use expensive tests?

47:24.000 --> 47:25.467
- This is no different

47:25.533 --> 47:27.467
than HMOs in the public sector.

47:27.533 --> 47:29.967
- There is a difference.

47:30.033 --> 47:31.300
The state has laws

47:31.367 --> 47:32.533
to protect consumers
against cuts

47:32.600 --> 47:33.834
in medical services.

47:33.900 --> 47:35.467
There are no such laws
for inmates.

47:35.533 --> 47:38.800
Weigert has no incentive
to provide quality care.

47:38.867 --> 47:41.300
- Look, we're both doctors.

47:41.367 --> 47:43.734
I mean, I took
the same oath you did.

47:43.800 --> 47:46.300
- Then why cut Miguel Alvarez's
antidepressants?

47:46.367 --> 47:48.967
- Because, as I told you,

47:49.033 --> 47:51.667
I consider this
unnecessary care.

47:51.734 --> 47:53.333
And if you hadn't spent
too much money

47:53.400 --> 47:55.667
on unnecessary care,

47:55.734 --> 47:57.333
the state wouldn't have had
to bring us in.

47:57.400 --> 47:59.533
- Alvarez is suicidal.

47:59.600 --> 48:01.367
- Well,
maybe it's all for the best.

48:01.433 --> 48:02.900
- What?

48:02.967 --> 48:07.333
- Well, God knows he's not doing
anyone any good alive.

48:07.400 --> 48:09.834
- Fuck you.

48:09.900 --> 48:11.300
- This interview is over.

48:11.367 --> 48:15.433
I'm hereby giving you
two weeks' notice.

48:15.500 --> 48:19.033
- Knock yourself out, asshole.

48:23.200 --> 48:25.467
[knocking]

48:25.533 --> 48:28.266
- Ray.
- Hi.

48:28.333 --> 48:31.100
- What's going on?
- Nothing.

48:31.166 --> 48:34.200
- Do I look especially gullible
to you today?

48:34.266 --> 48:36.200
You hide a sandwich
under your vestments,

48:36.266 --> 48:37.467
which you never wear,

48:37.533 --> 48:39.967
and I'm supposed to think
it's SOP?

48:40.033 --> 48:41.467
- Pete, I can't talk about it.

48:41.533 --> 48:45.734
- Oh, some confidentiality
between you and a prisoner.

48:45.800 --> 48:48.467
- I'm due in Solitary.

48:48.533 --> 48:50.967
- There's four Catholics
currently residing in Solitary.

48:51.033 --> 48:54.133
There's O'Brien.
There's Bevilaqua.

48:54.200 --> 48:57.900
Hevern. Alvarez.

48:59.834 --> 49:03.500
You're bringing food
that he likes to cheer him up.

49:03.567 --> 49:06.667
No, because then there's
no confidentiality problem.

49:06.734 --> 49:10.767
You're bringing food
to Alvarez because...

49:11.934 --> 49:14.266
Because he's not being fed.

49:16.367 --> 49:18.600
Because of what he did
to Officer Rivera,

49:18.667 --> 49:22.767
